                <h2>Serving Cranberry Township & Butler County</h2>
                <p>Cranberry Township has grown from a quiet crossroads into one of Western Pennsylvania's most dynamic communities — attracting young professionals, growing families, and a thriving business district. Ament Law Group serves Cranberry Township residents and business owners with the full range of estate planning, probate, real estate, and business law services.</p>

                <h2>Estate Planning</h2>
                <p>Cranberry Township's demographics skew toward working professionals and young families — exactly the clients who benefit most from proactive estate planning. We help Cranberry residents establish wills, revocable living trusts, powers of attorney, and healthcare directives that protect their families as their assets and circumstances evolve.</p>

                <h2>Probate Administration</h2>
                <p>Estates in Cranberry Township are administered through the Butler County Register of Wills. Our attorneys are experienced with Butler County procedures and guide executors through every step of the process, from initial filings through inheritance tax preparation and the final accounting.</p>

                <h2>Business Law</h2>
                <p>Cranberry's commercial growth has created a vibrant business community along Route 19 and the Turnpike corridor. We help business owners with entity formation, operating agreements, partnership agreements, commercial contracts, and ongoing compliance. Whether you're launching a startup or expanding an established business, we provide the legal framework for growth.</p>

                <h2>Real Estate</h2>
                <p>With Cranberry's active residential market and expanding commercial corridors, our title insurance and closing services are a natural fit for buyers, sellers, and developers in the area.</p>

